    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-05-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-09-02T19:04:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Extractive Industries Transparency Disclosure Act - Amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to instruct the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) to require specified annual reports of an issuer to disclose the total payments made to an agency or instrumentality of a foreign government: (1) for natural resources in a foreign country; or (2) in connection with the extraction of natural resources from a foreign country.</p><p>Requires compilation of such information so that it is accessible by the public directly from the SEC website without separately accessing the annual reports of each issuer filing the information on the EDGAR system.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Extractive Industries Transparency Disclosure Act</title>
